341 // Define operator overloads to enable bit operations on enum values that are
342 // used to define flags. Use DEFINE_ENUM_FLAG_OPERATORS(YOUR_TYPE) to enable these
343 // operators on YOUR_TYPE.
344 
345 // Moved here from objbase.w.
346 
347 // Templates are defined here in order to avoid a dependency on C++ <type_traits> header file,
348 // or on compiler-specific contructs.
349 extern "C++" {
350 
351  template <size_t S>
352  struct _ENUM_FLAG_INTEGER_FOR_SIZE;
353 
354  template <>
355  struct _ENUM_FLAG_INTEGER_FOR_SIZE<1>
356  {
357  typedef INT8 type;
358  };
359 
360  template <>
361  struct _ENUM_FLAG_INTEGER_FOR_SIZE<2>
362  {
363  typedef INT16 type;
364  };
365 
366  template <>
367  struct _ENUM_FLAG_INTEGER_FOR_SIZE<4>
368  {
369  typedef INT32 type;
370  };
371 
372  // used as an approximation of std::underlying_type<T>
373  template <class T>
374  struct _ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER
375  {
376  typedef typename _ENUM_FLAG_INTEGER_FOR_SIZE<sizeof(T)>::type type;
377  };
378 
379 }

381 #define DEFINE_ENUM_FLAG_OPERATORS(ENUMTYPE) \
382 extern "C++" { \
383 inline ENUMTYPE operator | (ENUMTYPE a, ENUMTYPE b) { return ENUMTYPE(((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)a) | ((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)b)); } \
384 inline ENUMTYPE &operator |= (ENUMTYPE &a, ENUMTYPE b) { return (ENUMTYPE &)(((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type &)a) |= ((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)b)); } \
385 inline ENUMTYPE operator & (ENUMTYPE a, ENUMTYPE b) { return ENUMTYPE(((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)a) & ((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)b)); } \
386 inline ENUMTYPE &operator &= (ENUMTYPE &a, ENUMTYPE b) { return (ENUMTYPE &)(((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type &)a) &= ((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)b)); } \
387 inline ENUMTYPE operator ~ (ENUMTYPE a) { return ENUMTYPE(~((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)a)); } \
388 inline ENUMTYPE operator ^ (ENUMTYPE a, ENUMTYPE b) { return ENUMTYPE(((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)a) ^ ((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)b)); } \
389 inline ENUMTYPE &operator ^= (ENUMTYPE &a, ENUMTYPE b) { return (ENUMTYPE &)(((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type &)a) ^= ((_ENUM_FLAG_SIZED_INTEGER<ENUMTYPE>::type)b)); } \
390 }

646 extern "C++"
647 {
648  template<typename T> _Post_equal_to_(pp) _Post_satisfies_(return == pp) void** IID_PPV_ARGS_Helper(T** pp)
649  {
650 #pragma prefast(suppress: 6269, "Tool issue with unused static_cast")
651  static_cast<IUnknown*>(*pp); // make sure everyone derives from IUnknown
652  return reinterpret_cast<void**>(pp);
653  }
654 }

2417 #define D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_MASK 0x7
2418 #define D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_SHIFT 3
2419 #define D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_ALWAYS_SET_BIT_AVOIDING_ZEROMEM_MISTAKES (1<<(D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_SHIFT*4))
2420 #define D3D12_ENCODE_SHADER_4_COMPONENT_MAPPING(Src0,Src1,Src2,Src3) ((((Src0)&D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_MASK)| \
2421  (((Src1)&D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_MASK)<<D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_SHIFT)| \
2422  (((Src2)&D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_MASK)<<(D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_SHIFT*2))| \
2423  (((Src3)&D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_MASK)<<(D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_SHIFT*3))| \
2424  D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_ALWAYS_SET_BIT_AVOIDING_ZEROMEM_MISTAKES))
2425 #define D3D12_DECODE_SHADER_4_COMPONENT_MAPPING(ComponentToExtract,Mapping) ((D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING)(Mapping >> (D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_SHIFT*ComponentToExtract) & D3D12_SHADER_COMPONENT_MAPPING_MASK))
2426 #define D3D12_DEFAULT_SHADER_4_COMPONENT_MAPPING D3D12_ENCODE_SHADER_4_COMPONENT_MAPPING(0,1,2,3)
